  <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary40.jpg"/>
            <dateline><date>Saturday 15.</date></dateline>
            <p>It was <name type="weather ">rainy, drizzling all day</name>. About ten o'clock we had regimental drill
               and marched down along the beach &amp; visited all the batteries. At the lower
               one they were digging <objectName type="nature ">trenches</objectName>, making <objectName>bridges</objectName>, drains and putting up a
               telegraph up this way. We returned up the <objectName>road</objectName> about three o'clock hungry
               enough to eat a good dinner. <persName cert="high" key="Dick Coulter" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper025" type="real">Dick</persName> had ready for us of <objectName>roast potatoes, fried beef, coffee and butter &amp; crackers</objectName>. Yesterday up at [Loes?] he showed us
               some <objectName>fig trees</objectName> - they resembled in appearance <objectName type="food">horse chestnut</objectName>, not in leaf. Our
               cooks were ordered on board to cook three days provisions and have them ready
               by tomorrow evening. We understand that we are to go on some expedition and
               return here - our camp equipage is to come on <objectName type="nature ">shore</objectName>. </p>
         </div>
      </body>
  </text>
